snippet: At least two car bombs shattered a building that houses the local headquarters of the Kurdistan Democratic Party in Kirkuk, and a third exploded nearby.
abstract: Iraqi police say at least two car bombs shattered building housing local headquarters of Kurdistan Democratic Party in restive city of Kirkuk, killing at least 19 people and wounding more than 200.
lead_paragraph: At least two car bombs shattered a building that houses the local headquarters of the Kurdistan Democratic Party in Kirkuk, and a third exploded nearby.

headline.seo: In Iraq, Bombers Kill More Than 20 in Kirkuk
headline.main: Bombings in Iraq Kill More Than 20 and Are Seen as Political
headline.print_headline: Bombings in Iraq Kill More Than 20 and Are Seen as Political
